## Dead Ends
- Considered committing .claude/settings.local.json so hooks ship to all
  developers. Rejected because the file's literal name implies "local"
  and Claude Code's convention is that .local.json files are per-machine.
- Considered using `vercel env add ... --target preview` syntax. The CLI
  doesn't have a --target flag for this command (the env is a positional
  argument). Confirmed via `vercel env add --help` and the JSON action_required
  output.
- Considered making agent-verify.sh poll vercel CLI output instead of the
  REST API. Rejected because the CLI's output format is unstable across
  versions and matching by commit SHA is more robust than parsing branch
  aliases (Vercel slugifies long branch names in non-obvious ways).

## Hints for Future Agents
- The Vercel auth token lives at ~/.local/share/com.vercel.cli/auth.json
  (NOT ~/.vercel/auth.json — that path is empty). jq -r .token reads it.
- Vercel's /v6/deployments endpoint accepts meta-githubCommitSha as a
  query filter. Returns up to `limit` recent matches. Use this to bind
  a Vercel deploy to a specific git commit unambiguously.
- PROMPTIONARY_MOCK_GEMINI is checked in TWO places:
    1. lib/gemini.ts:5-31 — server-side, gates the actual Gemini calls.
       Must be set in Vercel Preview env for previews to honor it.
       (Set as env id bR91jXZs75XH22eF.)
    2. tests/e2e/full-round-mocked.spec.ts (and similar) — gates
       test.skip(). Must be set in the Playwright runner's env so the
       mocked specs actually execute. agent-verify.sh sets it locally
       for the runner.
- .greenhouse/state.jsonl tracks ingest+dispatch attempts. After a clean
  re-run, expect runs to be marked failed initially because dispatch (ov
  coordinator start) hadn't been wired before this PR. Use
  `mv state.jsonl state.jsonl.bak; touch state.jsonl` to reset.
- The 18 issues currently in .seeds/ were ingested by greenhouse from
  GH and have seedsIds like promptionary-3470. Inspect with
  `sd list` after the PR merges.
- Mulch's expertise records use foundational classification for
  conventions confirmed across many sessions; tactical for one-shot
  patterns; observational for unverified hypotheses. Future agents
  should follow this — see the seeded records as templates.

## Codebase Discoveries
- The Promptionary repo's existing playwright.config.ts uses
  PROMPTIONARY_TEST_URL as the base URL override. agent-verify.sh
  sets this to the Vercel preview URL, so no playwright config changes
  needed.
- .overstory/.gitignore uses a wildcard+whitelist pattern (`*` then
  `!.gitignore`, `!config.yaml`, etc.) — auto-healed by `ov prime` per
  its comment. Don't normalize this to "ignore the runtime stuff
  explicitly" because the tool re-emits it.
- .seeds/issues.jsonl already had 18 ingested issues from greenhouse's
  poll cycle earlier in the session. Those are real seeds tasks now
  (seedsIds visible in .greenhouse/state.jsonl). When the PR merges and
  greenhouse polls again, it will detect them as already-ingested
  (idempotency on ghIssueId).

